name: De /wʊlf/
description: "The famously known myth is a grey wolf would howl at the moon. The idea of the two entities sit side by side, which inspires this piece. Now, expand your imagination. Our eyes are the wolf’s. In the dark woods, cold breeze blows the fur, its eyes looking up in between the trees. Staring at the night light. Howling, marking territories. Hailing, ready to hunt under the light of the moon. Heart is thumping fast. In a split second, an atrocious event will happen. Now. Wake up." By @baimtje
